## Git protocol — temporal preservation

Carnatic music has endured because each generation transmitted it faithfully and completely.
Git is our instrument of faithful, complete transmission. **Every agent commits and pushes
their own work at the end of every session in which files changed.**

### Pre-commit checklist
- [ ] `git diff --stat` reviewed — no unintended files staged
- [ ] `bani-render` run if `musicians.json` or `compositions.json` changed (graph.html must be current)
- [ ] No debug output left in scripts
- [ ] `carnatic/.clinerules` Open questions section updated
- [ ] Commit message follows format below
- [ ] `git push` executed after commit

### Commit message format
```
<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary, ≤72 chars>

<body: what changed and why>
[AGENTS: <comma-separated agent slugs>]
```

**Type vocabulary:** `data` · `tool` · `render` · `schema` · `fix` · `chore` · `branch`
**Scope vocabulary:** `lineage` · `node` · `recording` · `composition` · `toolchain` · `config`

### Branching policy
- **`main`** — always stable; every commit must pass the pre-commit checklist
- **`experiment/<name>`** — schema experiments or rendering pipeline rewrites
- **`data/<name>`** — large batch data imports pending review
- Merge via `git merge --no-ff`; delete branch after merge

---

## Bundle schema (v1)  ← ADR-083 reference

Schema contract for `bani_add_bundle.json` (browser→disk write channel). Full spec: `plans/ADR-083-bani-add-bundle-canonical-write-channel.md`.

**Envelope** (every bundle must have these top-level keys):
```json
{ "schema_version": 1, "generated_at": "<ISO-8601 UTC>", "items": { … } }
```

**Whitelisted item type keys** (in fixed processing order):
`ragas` → `composers` → `musicians` → `compositions` → `recordings` → `edges`

Any other key under `items` is a hard-error: `bani_add.py` exits 1 before processing any items.

**Version gate**: `schema_version > MAX_VERSION (1)` → immediate refusal with upgrade hint.
Additive field additions (new optional field on an existing item) do NOT bump the version.

**`addToBundle(type, obj)`** in `entry_forms.js` throws `Error("addToBundle: unknown type '…'")` on a non-whitelisted type — no silent drops.

**`MusicianItem` discriminator** (`type` field, required):
- `"new"` — create musician node + seed `youtube[]`
- `"youtube_append"` — append `youtube[]` entries to existing musician

**`YoutubeEntryItem`** shape is byte-equivalent to one on-disk `node.youtube[]` element (recital track or lecdem — see ADR-077 for `kind`/`subjects` fields). The ingester forwards all keys to `writer.add_youtube` (transport, not translator).

